Carles Mateu, a man who refused to speak in Spanish during a routine traffic
test in Valencia, was sentenced to six months in prison and had his driver's
license revoked for disobeying authorities.

![CarlesMateu](https://ca.globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2013/10/CarlesMateu.jpg)

“WE ARE ALL CARLES MATEU / Group supporting the driver sentenced to 6 months
in prison in Valencia.” Poster from the group supporting Carles Mateu in the
town of Alemenara (Castelló).

Mateu was driving his car in December 2012 when the [Civil
Guard](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civil_Guard_%28Spain%29), the federal
military guard of Spain, stopped him for a routine traffic stop in [Castelló
](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Province_of_Castell%C3%B3n)([Valencia](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valencian_Community)).
But he was detained for three hours by two agents, who accused him of refusing
to submit to a breathalyzer test and of not wearing a seat belt nor a
reflective vest. Mateu, however, claims that these reports are false and the
agents sanctioned him for speaking to them in
[Valencian](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valencian), a [regional
dialect](http://ca.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dialectes_del_catal%C3%A0) [ca] of
[Catalan](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catalan_language) that is spoken in the
territory, and refusing to express himself in Spanish.

The [Valencian language](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valencian) holds
official status in the region along with Spanish, just as in
[Catalonia](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catalonia) and the [Balearic
Islands](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balearic_Islands). According to online
news publication [La Veu del País
Valencià](http://www.laveupv.com/noticia/4808/carles-mateu-la-sentencia-de-
preso-es-una-repressio-contra-la-llengua) [ca], Mateu felt that the agents
were displaying signs of “contempt” toward him and his language, using phrases
like “speak to me in Spanish, we are in Spain.”

Mateu [was acquitted](http://www.ara.cat/paisvalencia/denuncia-valencia-
Guardia_Civil-Almenara-Carles_Mateu-judici_0_849515176.html) [ca] in January
2013, but the district attorney appealed and the sentence was revoked. At the
same time, Mateu's previous countersuit against the agents’ false accusations
was thrown out. The [new sentence](http://www.ara.cat/paisvalencia/conductor-
Almenara-multa-Guardia_Civil-catala_0_996500616.html) [ca] issued on September
20, 2013 condemns him to six months in prison and the suspension of his
driver's license for a year and a day.

**A victim turned into offender**

The case has attracted much interest, both civil and political, along the
Catalan-speaking territories, given that many view it as one more case of
discrimination with linguistic motives, similar to those [reported
](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2013/08/24/three-youths-harassed-after-
speaking-catalan-at-music-festival-in-spain/)at music festival Arenal Sound
last summer. In an
[interview](http://www.elpuntavui.cat/noticia/article/3-politica/-/680529-ara-
veig-com-el-meu-pais-viu-una-persecucio-danys.html) [ca] with Catalan
newspaper [_El Punt Avui_ ,](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/El_Punt) Mateu
explains:

> He de dir que vaig reaccionar com qualsevol persona a qui intenten furtar el
> seu dret a la lliure expressió i vaig reaccionar –ho dic sincerament i amb
> el cor a la mà– per sota de la pressió a què els dos agents em van sotmetre.

> I must say that I reacted just like anyone else whose right to free
> expression was taken away, and I reacted—I say this sincerely, with my hand
> to my heart—under the pressure I was subject to by those two agents.

![CarlesMateu2](https://ca.globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2013/10/CarlesMateu2-400x300.jpg)

“I, TOO, POSSESS THE FLAW OF SPEAKING VALENCIAN.” Shared image on Twitter from
Alícia (@marclia), professor of Catalan at the University of Valencia.

Mateu's lawyer explained to digital newspaper
[VilaWeb](http://www.vilaweb.cat/noticia/4145138/20130920/conductor-negar-
parlar-espanyol-condemnat-preso.html) [ca] that the [linguistic
conflict](http://ca.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conflicte_ling%C3%BC%C3%ADstic) [ca] is
now considered Mateu's strategy for slowing down the breathalyzer test, which
converts the victim into the offender.

**We are all Carles Mateu**

Demonstrations of solidarity have multiplied online. A Facebook page, [Jo
També Sóc Carles Mateu](https://www.facebook.com/pages/Jo-
tamb%C3%A9-s%C3%B3c-Carles-Mateu/462622320464523) [ca] (I, too, am Carles
Mateu), collects messages of support.

On Twitter, many users showed their discontent with the hashtag
[#TotSomCarlesMateu](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23TotssomCarlesMateu&src=hash)
(We are all Carles Mateu). [Antoni
Manyanós](http://www.ecosfera.cat/blogs/antoni-manyanos) [ca]
([@amanyanos](https://twitter.com/amanyanos)), professor of geography and
history, says:

> El País Valencià un lloc on el règim espanyol et pot condembar [sic] a presó
> per parlar valencià amb la Guàrdia Civil
> [#TotssomCarlesMateu](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23TotssomCarlesMateu&src=hash)
> [#Prou](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Prou&src=hash)
>
> — Antoni #soseducació (@amanyanos) [September 24,
> 2013](https://twitter.com/amanyanos/statuses/382539256088248320)

> Valencia, a place where the Spanish regime can condemn you to prison for
> speaking in Valencian with the Civil Guard
> [#WeAreAllCarlesMateu](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23TotssomCarlesMateu&src=hash)
> [#Enough](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Prou&src=hash)

Valencian journalist Amàlia Garrigós
([@AmaliaGarrigos](https://twitter.com/AmaliaGarrigos) [ca/es]) encouraged her
followers to sign a petition on
[Change.org](http://www.change.org/es/peticiones/que-los-cuerpos-de-seguridad-
del-estado-se-expresen-en-catal%C3%A1n) [es] for Spanish security guards in
the territory to speak in Catalan:

> Un conductor valencià condemnat per parlar en la seua llengua. Signeu? Jo ja
> ho he fet!
> [#TotsSomCarlesMateu](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23TotsSomCarlesMateu&src=hash)
> <http://t.co/g33L4XeCWK>
>
> — Amàlia Garrigós (@AmaliaGarrigos) [September 20,
> 2013](https://twitter.com/AmaliaGarrigos/statuses/381102192209297409)

> A Valencian driver sentenced for speaking in his own language. Will you sign
> this petition? I just did!
> [#WeAreAllCarlesMateu](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23TotsSomCarlesMateu&src=hash)
> <http://t.co/g33L4XeCWK>

Moreover, a
[group](http://www.vilaweb.cat/noticia/4146559/20130928/concentracio-almenara-
suport-carles-mateu.html) [ca] supporting Mateu was organized in his town of
[Almenara](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Almenara,_Castell%C3%B3n), and a
petition on [Change.org](http://www.change.org/es/peticiones/s%C3%ADndic-de-
greuges-de-la-comunitat-valenciana-retirada-de-la-pena-de-pres%C3%B3-a-carles-
mateu-blay-per-parlar-valenci%C3%A0-a-la-gu%C3%A0rdia-civil) [es] has gathered
more than 11,500 signatures to demand the sentence be withdrawn.

**Political reactions  
**

Carles Mateu's case arrived at the Spanish Parliament thanks to the
representatives [Joan Baldoví](http://joanbaldovi.com/) [ca] of the [Coalició
Compromís](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comprom%C3%ADs) (Compromise
Coalition), and [Joan Tardà](http://blocs.esquerra.cat/joan-tarda) [ca], of
[Esquerra Republicana de
Catalunya](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republican_Left_of_Catalonia)
(Republican Left Party) (ERC). Baldoví [said
](http://www.laveupv.com/noticia/5004/baldovi-si-mateu-va-a-la-preso-per-
parlar-valencia-lestat-espanyol-es-posara-al-nivell-de-)that it would be
“barbaric” to send a citizen to prison for speaking his own language, while
Tardà formulated many questions for the Ministry of the Interior.

[Ramon
Tremosa](http://www.europarl.europa.eu/meps/en/97203/Ramon_TREMOSA%20i%20BALCELLS_home.html;jsessionid=CADD050121E952DF46D7547957AFD9EA.node1),
a member of the European Parliament representing the Catalan moderate right-
wing ruling party, [Convergència i
Unió](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Converg%C3%A8ncia_i_Uni%C3%B3), reported
the case to the European Commission with the support of opposition parties
[ERC ](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republican_Left_of_Catalonia)and [ICV-
EUIA](http://ca.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iniciativa_per_Catalunya_Verds_-
_Esquerra_Unida_i_Alternativa) [ca]:

> Ara entrem pregunta a Comissió Europa contra condemna Carles Mateu pel
> català. La signem [@ciu](https://twitter.com/ciu)
> [@Esquerra_ERC](https://twitter.com/Esquerra_ERC) i
> [@icveuia](https://twitter.com/icveuia)
> [#TotssomCarlesMateu](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23TotssomCarlesMateu&src=hash)
>
> — Ramon Tremosa (@ramontremosa) [September 24,
> 2013](https://twitter.com/ramontremosa/statuses/382541452582338561)

> Now we will ask the European Commission about the sentence against Carles
> Mateu for speaking Catalan. The undersigned: [@ciu](https://twitter.com/ciu)
> [@Esquerra_ERC](https://twitter.com/Esquerra_ERC) i
> [@icveuia](https://twitter.com/icveuia)
> [#WeAreAllCarlesMateu](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23TotssomCarlesMateu&src=hash)

**Rising awareness to stop** **language conflict**

Josep Escribano, president of [El Tempir](http://www.eltempir.cat/) [cat], a
civic association for the language,
[encouraged](http://www.laveupv.com/noticia/5098/josep-escribano-es-necessari-
fer-visibles-els-casos-dagressio-linguistica) [ca] people to report cases of
linguistic discrimination to generate social pressure.

Escribano [argues](http://www.laveupv.com/noticia/5098/josep-escribano-es-
necessari-fer-visibles-els-casos-dagressio-linguistica) [ca] that the language
supremacy of Spanish has allowed, over time, for Catalan-speaking people to
interiorize their prejudice toward their own language, considering it of an
inferior status. But he remains optimistic:

> Cada vegada més, la gent que és ferma i que té una lleialtat lingüística,
> que s'estima el país i que s'estima la llengua, està fent un pas endavant i
> ho denuncia.

> More and more, people who are strong and have a linguistic loyalty, people
> who love the Catalan nation and love the Catalan language, are taking a step
> forward and reporting cases of this kind of discrimination.

By making these cases of linguistic discrimination public, citizens receive
support from the entities defending the language and from the community, which
facilitates the [linguistic
normalization](http://ca.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normalitzaci%C3%B3_ling%C3%BC%C3%ADstica)
[ca] and [universal linguistic
rights](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Universal_Declaration_of_Linguistic_Rights)
of Catalan's use.

